A 14-year-old boy was injured in a shooting in the Tampa Heights area Tuesday night, according to a spokesperson for the Tampa Police Department. Police responded to a report of a shooting in the 200 block of East Nordica Street just before 11 p.m. and found the 14-year-old with a gunshot wound. The teen was taken to a local hospital, where he was in stable condition Wednesday, police said. Police said they do not believe the shooting was a random act. No other information was released.